# Copy to .env and fill in. .env is gitignored.

# Phase 1 currently has no required runtime secrets:
#   - Deploys go through the Netlify <-> GitHub integration on push to `main`,
#     so no NETLIFY_AUTH_TOKEN is needed.
#   - LLM work (audit CTA-above-fold check, scrape extraction, copy generation)
#     is done manually inside Claude Code sessions, so no ANTHROPIC_API_KEY
#     is needed. See CLAUDE.md for the operator-facing handoff points.
#
# Add a key here if a later phase needs programmatic API access. Examples:
# NETLIFY_AUTH_TOKEN=    # for src/lib/netlify.py if we move off git-driven deploys
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=     # for src/lib/llm.py if we automate the LLM steps
